Using @{b}configure@{ub}
***************

@{b}   configure@{ub} prepares source directories for building programs in them.
"Configuring" is the process of preparing software to compile
correctly on a given @{i}host@{ui}, for a given @{i}target@{ui}.

@{b}   configure@{ub} subsequently writes a configured @{b}Makefile@{ub} from a pre-built
template; @{b}configure@{ub} uses variables that have been set in the
configuring process to determine the values of some variables in the
@{b}Makefile@{ub}.  Because of this we will refer to both @{b}configure@{ub} variables
and @{b}Makefile@{ub} variables.  This convention allows us to determine where
the variable should be set initially, in either @{b}configure.in@{ub} or
@{b}Makefile.in@{ub}.


